{"lemma":"كُلُّ","slug":"كُلُّ","root":"ك.ل.ل","root_slug":"ك-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كُلّ","root":"كلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":359},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43082","n43085","n43086"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"each one, everyone"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"each, every (with following indefinite noun in the genitive)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"whole, all (with following definite noun in the genitive)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Akkadian 𒆕𒀀𒁉 (kalûm), Ge'ez ኵል (kʷəll), Ugaritic 𐎋𐎍 (kl), Phoenician 𐤊𐤋 (kl), Classical Syriac ܟܾܠ (kul). From Proto-Semitic *kʷall- or Proto-Semitic *kull-, ultimately from Proto-Afroasiatic *ʔa-kʷall-."},"ipa":["/kull/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43082","headword_ar":"كَلَّ","root":"kl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the sight)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, dim, dull,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hebetated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, fatigued, tired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wearied."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~ati AlA^ayodiY","text_ar":"كَلَّتِ الاَيْدِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arms, became weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DEft","text_ar":"ضعفت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEaufato","text_ar":"ضَعَُفَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ham, 296.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~a Eano fiEolK","text_ar":"كَلَّ عَنْ فِعْلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was fatigued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak, and so disabled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incapacitated, from doing a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyaA Eanohu","text_ar":"اَعْيَا عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEaufa Eanohu","text_ar":"ضَعَُفَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuxiba","text_ar":"نُخِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earisa","text_ar":"عَرِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~ato A^asonaAnuhu","text_ar":"كَلَّتْ اَسْنَانُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drs","text_ar":"ضرس"},{"kind":"text","text":",) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAlN","text_ar":"كَلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, in that art.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His teeth were set on edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK, in that art.,) by eating, or drinking, what was acid, or sour. (S, K, in that art.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~a","text_ar":"كَلَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a sword, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was blunt, and would not cut."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, &c.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~atuhun~a","text_ar":"كُلَّتُهُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~uhun~a","text_ar":"كُلُّهُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see Bd xxxi., last verse."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43085","headword_ar":"كَلٌّ","root":"kl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A burden;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viqolN","text_ar":"ثِقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons, whom one has to support:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eay~alN","text_ar":"عَيَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaAlN","text_ar":"عِيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) applied to one and to more. (Msb.) See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(last sentence but two)."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n43086","headword_ar":"كُلٌّ","root":"kl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"when preceded by a negative and followed by an exception, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur, xxxviii. 13,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino kul~N A_il~aA ka*~aba Alr~usula","text_ar":"اـِنْ كُلٌّ اـِلَّا كَذَّبَ الرُّسُلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There was not any one but accused the apostles of lying."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also another ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lam~aA","text_ar":"لَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoD","text_ar":"بَعْض"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa AlEaAlimu kul~u AlEaAlimi","text_ar":"هُوَ العَالِمُ كُلُّ العَالِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the possessor of knowledge, the entirety of the possessor of knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means that he is one who has attained to the utmost degree of the quality thus attributed to him. (Sb, K, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amaA","text_ar":"كُلَّمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whatever."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amaA","text_ar":"كُلَّمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whenever; as often as; every time that; in proportion as."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amano","text_ar":"كُلَّمَنْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoever."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}